rComments: Class wasn't hard but extremely disorganized. She reused information from previous years on her class website and it showed (she many times forget to change the dates). She also loved to give out tons of little petty assignments. Lastly, she was very bias in her opinion and didn't like it when students disagreed. Overall, the class was pretty easy.

I can't say enough good things about her! I wasn't sure about international relations before, but she showed me that it's a really cool field to get into, and she helped me figure out a few study abroad options that I'll definitely be looking into this summer.

She's truly amazing at what she does! With tons of international experience, she brings in a global perspective like no other global studies professor I've had. Everyone in my class thought she was great, and we found ourselves very engaged in a wide array of topics.
